cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper discusses the quality and software development management of Initial Coin Offerings (ICO) and their relationship with Ethereum Smart Contract Environment. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper discusses the security and cryptography aspects of ICOs, the software development management of Smart Contracts, the distributed computing environment of Ethereum blockchain, and the social and economic impact of ICOs.
